##NEW CHAMPION PNEUMONIA CONVALESCENT PLASMA INTO "life-saving Straw" ? Treatment of 11 critically ill patients is effective, but the risk can not be ignored

On the evening of February 13, the Chinese medicine Chinese biology announced an important development, in the new cap pneumonia convalescent plasma has detected the high titer virus neutralizing antibody, the experiment proves, can effectively kill the new cap virus, "We treated 11 critically ill patients with convalescent plasma, and the results were remarkable, " the Chinese biology official said.

Lu Hongzhou, a member of the Expert Group of the National Health Commission, said in this regard that Shanghai is ready to carry out plasma therapy. One patient has already prepared to use the plasma of a convalescent patient, and the plasma therapy is already very mature, plasma therapy is particularly valuable in the absence of specific drugs for the novel coronavirus.

The plasma product of Xinguangtemian was prepared by inactivating virus, neutralizing antibody against Xinguangtemian virus and detecting multiple pathogenic microorganisms.

Zhong Nanshan had predicted that the NCP epidemic would peak in mid to late February, and as of 2400 hours on February 13, the National Health Commission had reported a cumulative total of 63,851 confirmed cases (1043 cases in Hubei Province) , there were 6723 cured cases (269 reduced cases in Hubei Province) and 1380 died cases (108 reduced cases in Hubei Province) . The situation remains critical.

In the absence of vaccines and specific therapeutic drugs, plasma therapy can improve the clinical treatment of severe cases, reduce mortality, this is undoubtedly a great deal of good news.

But there are always two sides to things, new coronavirus immune plasma products and immune globulin preparation for the whole situation can bring much change?

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure | a caring person donated blood in hospital during the anti-epidemic period (Source: Hefei Evening News) 

Experts recommend blood donation from ex-patients

It is reported that at present, Chinese biology has accelerated the preparation of novel coronavirus-specific Immune Plasma Products and Immunoglobulin, and in close cooperation with the China Institute of Biological Products, the SINOPHARM group Wuhan Blood Products Co. , Ltd. , the First People's Hospital of Wuhan Jiangxia District, the Wuhan Blood Center, the Wuhan Institute of Virology of the Chinese Academy of Sciences, and the China Institute of Food and Drug Control, into the clinical care of critically ill patients.

According to the circular of the National Board of Health on the issuance of the fifth edition of the Protocol for the diagnosis and treatment of pneumonia with COVID-19 infection, it is suggested that the convalescent plasma therapy can be used in the treatment of severe and critical cases.

Starting from January 20, China biology set up the relevant team, mobilized the relevant equipment and raw materials, and carried out the collection of plasma from the recovered patients with NCP in Wuhan area. On February 8, the first phase of the new Guante free plasma treatment was carried out in three critical patients at Jiangxia District First People's Hospital, and more than 10 critical patients are currently being treated in subsequent hospitals.

Clinical response, 12 to 24 hours after treatment, the laboratory detection of major inflammatory indicators significantly decreased, the proportion of lymphocyte increased, Oxygenation, viral load and other key indicators, clinical signs and symptoms significantly improved. Experts said that from the clinical pathological process, most of the new coronary pneumonia patients after treatment and rehabilitation, the body will produce specific antibodies against the new coronavirus, can kill and eliminate the virus.

China's biological research and development related officials said that the new coronavirus immune plasma collection, preparation and series of detection process, with good security, preparation technology mature, the time required is short. At present, in the absence of vaccine and specific therapeutic drugs, the use of this special immune plasma products is the most effective way to treat new coronavirus infection, can significantly reduce the mortality rate of critical patients.

Zhang Dingyu, director of Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital, also mentioned it at the 23rd press conference on the prevention and control of the new coronavirus epidemic in Hubei Province held on the evening of February 13 in response to questions from reporters on how to improve treatment and reduce mortality, the increase in the number of severe and critically ill patients has led to a slight increase in the absolute number of deaths, mainly among the elderly and some patients with underlying diseases.

Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital is a designated hospital for the treatment of severe new coronary pneumonia. At present, the hospital is carrying out the transfusion of convalescent plasma of convalescent patients.

Zhang Dingyu's initiative, "because recovered patients have a large number of synthetic antibodies against the virus, and I would like to appeal to some patients who have recovered to come to our hospital and give your arm and precious plasma, and we will come together to save these patients who are still struggling with the disease. "

Some details are contained in China biosciences'new initiative on plasma donation for patients recovering from coronary pneumonia. For example, patients who have recovered from an infection and are in good health after discharge from the hospital should be aged between 18 and 60 years and have been diagnosed with COVID-19 infection Need to be in the blood donation site after registration, health consultation, physical examination, meet the requirements for Plasma Collection (about 20-30 minutes) ; the day before as far as possible light diet, can not donate plasma on an empty stomach, women can not donate plasma during menstruation; After plasma donation, patients should press the puncture point for 20-30 minutes, pay attention to the eye of the needle, do not scrub with water, and maintain a healthy lifestyle after blood donation, donate plasma again after 14 days.

Deeptech called the blood donor office to learn that according to the blood donation law of the People's Republic of China and the relevant provisions of the health inspection requirements for blood donors, whole blood donors can donate 400 ml, or 300 ml, or 200 ml of whole blood each time. Plasma collection for patients recovering from new coronary pneumonia in Wuhan will give priority to local patients who can come from nearby. As of press time, there are many consultation calls, and the staff need to make preliminary screening judgments, no one has yet come to the hospital to donate blood, but we believe that a caring blood donor will soon come to our aid.

It wouldn't be the first time

This is not the first time that the blood of a recovered person has been used to fight an infectious disease outbreak and to treat a critically ill patient.

During the SARS epidemic in 2003, Beijing, Hong Kong and other places successfully treated many critical SARS patients with the serum of convalescent SARS patients, and confirmed that the antibody of convalescent SARS patients had therapeutic effect, in addition, 200 to 400 ML of plasma donated by a convalescent will not have much impact on health. The test items usually include ALT, HBSAG, anti-HCV, anti-HIV, syphilis, hemoglobin, blood type, total plasma protein and so on.

However, there was a key problem in the clinical use of convalescent Sera from SARS patients. At that time, some experts in the industry believed that although blood group compatibility tests and detection of pathogenic microorganisms such as Hepatitis A, hepatitis B, Hepatitis C, AIDS and Treponema Pallidum were conducted, however, there are still unknown pathogenic microorganisms in the patient's convalescent plasma, even the potential risk of SARS coronavirus infection, so there is the possibility of blood-borne diseases.

Jiang Suchun, a professor at the 302 Hospital of the People's Liberation Army, said the use of antibodies produced by SARS survivors to help kill the SARS virus in critically ill SARS patients was a lifesaving measure during a special period when there was neither a specific drug nor a vaccine. It should be noted that China has a sound blood management system, blood management regulations, through China's implementation of the test of 7 indicators, the basic ability to ensure blood safety.

In addition, multiple monoclonal and polyclonal antibody preparations with neutralizing activity inhibit MERS in preclinical models, according to a WHO summary of MERS coronavirus (Mers) .

However, there are no definitive data on the use of these agents or convalescent plasma to treat patients with MERS virus infection, only a systematic review and exploratory analysis of patients treated with convalescent plasma for Severe Mers virus showed a reduction in mortality, so convalescent plasma was considered a potential treatment. However, convalescent plasma, especially with defined levels of neutralizing antibodies to mers-cov, remains extremely limited.

What's the difference between the plasma and the serum? Plasma, in short, is a supernatant obtained by centrifuging the blood with an anticoagulant that blocks the clotting process and fibrinogen is present in the Plasma. Therefore, the chemical composition of plasma, water accounted for 90% ~ 92% , the other 10% to solute plasma protein-based, and contains salt, nutrients, enzymes, hormones, cholesterol and other elements.

Serum (Serum) is a yellowish transparent liquid formed in the upper layer after blood coagulation in vitro. The main response to coagulation is the conversion of fibrinogen to Fibrin, so the serum no longer contains fibrinogen, which is the biggest difference with plasma. However, a large number of substances that do not participate in the coagulation reaction are basically the same as plasma.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure | difference between serum and plasma extracted from blood (Source: Wikibiology)

In fact, many diseases caused by virus infection do not have specific drugs to treat and prevent, these diseases are mostly self-limiting, that is, the body through the immune response such as antibody to eliminate the virus.

By infusing the convalescent's plasma or serum, critically ill patients can obtain the assistance of foreign antibodies, thus obtaining passive protection.

In fact, more than 100 years ago, humans began to use serum therapy to fight bacterial infections.

1891, a German doctor, Emir Emil Adolf von Behring, injects a serum containing Diphtheria antitoxin into a dying child at the pediatric ward of the University Clinic in Berlin on Dec. 10. The next day, the child's condition improved significantly. This is an important milestone in the history of medicine, opening a new way to prevent and treat infectious diseases.

Emil Adolf von Behring won the first Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine in 1901 for his theoretical and clinical success in proving the efficacy of serum therapy against diphtheria and tetanus.

Risks that should not be ignored

The story of how antibodies extracted from the immune's blood were used to treat patients and eventually overcome the disease is often seen in science fiction movies, but can it be replicated in the current epidemic?

Technically, there is no difficulty in extracting new coronavirus-specific Plasma. The key factor is the concentration of antibodies, first of all, after the patient recovers, to determine that he has not carried the virus, such as through several nucleic acid tests have been negative, and second of all, the antibody test, to see how much virus antibodies in the body of the convalescent, for it to be therapeutic, the antibodies have to be in a certain amount and concentration; finally, the plasma is extracted to produce an antiviral component.

Further extraction of effective antibodies from the blood is difficult in practice. Studies have shown that recovery patients produce antigen specific B cells, and by screening and capturing these antigen specific b cells, and then sequence amplification and analysis, we can get effective whole human monoclonal antibody sequences, then you can make antibodies in vitro.

Further extraction of effective antibodies from the blood is difficult in practice. Studies have shown that recovering patients produce antigen-specific b cells, which are then screened and captured for sequence amplification and analysis, to produce an effective monoclonal antibody sequence for antibody preparation. While Antigen specific B cells are rare in the peripheral blood, in one study only 19 out of 500000 antigen specific b cells were isolated in the blood.

In addition, viral proteins contain a variety of heterologous proteins, for any heterologous protein, the human body is likely to produce specific antibodies against it, cOVID-19 can produce many different types of antibodies against the virus, but many lack antiviral activity, and only antibodies that target proteins on the surface of the virus are likely to have an antiviral effect.

It should not be overlooked that the use of convalescent plasma treatment also implies certain risks and limitations.

The practical experience of SARS and Mers shows that there are two important preconditions: First, control of the safety, complexity and risk of treatment with serum or immunized plasma, and the fact that the first convalescent patients with NCP have only recently recovered, our knowledge and function of the components of the convalescent blood are not well understood, so there may still be a risk of injecting the treated plasma directly into someone else;

Second, Plasma with compliant levels of antibodies to the virus itself is very limited, and blood type matching needs to be carried out, unable to cope with the tens of thousands of confirmed patients, clinical may only be applied to a small number of critically ill patients experimental treatment more practical, that is why the current strategy of isolation and treatment has focused on clinical trials of rapidly acting drugs or advancing vaccine development after virus strains have been isolated, most patients do not actually require serum antibodies or immune plasma therapy.

In addition, some clinicians said that the unpurified antibodies, along with blood transfusions into patients, for patients, is a strong foreign antigen, the organism will enter the body for a strong rejection of foreign substances. In other words, the result of direct infusion of antibodies into the blood is likely to cause acute graft rejection in the recipient, and a large number of immune inflammatory factors and antibodies against foreign substances appear in the patient's body within a short period of time, blood cells in the blood agglutinate reaction, the body multi-organ failure and life-threatening.

Therefore, the use of convalescent plasma for clinical use is only a life-saving measure in the special period with no specific drugs and no vaccine at present, and is only a special treatment for a small number of critically ill patients.
